</table><para id="fs-id1169596435756">We can find more solutions to the equation by substituting in any value of <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> or any value of <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> and solving the resulting equation to get another ordered pair that is a solution. There are infinitely many solutions of this equation.</para>
<example id="fs-id1169596437438">
<exercise id="fs-id1169596437440">
<problem id="fs-id1169596437443">
<para id="fs-id1169596437445">Complete <link target-id="fs-id1169596468299"/> to find three solutions to the equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>.</para>
