this is the equation solved: y equals 5. Below this is the ordered pair (negative 1, 5). Below this is the equation y equals negative 3x plus 2 again. Below this is the equation with negative 1 and 5 substituted for x and y, ready to be checked: 5 might equal negative 3 times negative 1 plus 2. Below this is 5 might equal 3 plus 2. Below this is 5 equals 5, with a check mark next to it."><label/><tgroup cols="6">
